President Biden visited the Pfizer manufacturing site in Kalamazoo, Michigan and made remarks about the administration's efforts to combat the COVID-19 pandemic. He thanked the workers for their work in producing vaccines and assured them that the government is doing everything possible to distribute and administer the vaccines. He also emphasized the importance of following public health guidelines, such as wearing masks and practicing social distancing, while vaccines are being distributed. President Biden discussed the American Rescue Plan and called on Congress to pass it to provide economic relief to those affected by the pandemic. He expressed hope that the country will return to normalcy by the end of the year, but acknowledged that there are still challenges ahead.